SIMPLE: simnel
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Simnel
<hw>Sim"nel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>simenel</ets> cake or bread of wheat flour, LL.
<ets>simenellus</ets> wheat bread, fr. L. <ets>simila</ets> the finest
wheat flour. Cf. <er>Semolina</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of
cake made of fine flour; a cracknel.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not common bread, but vastel bread, or <qex>simnels</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of rich plum cake, eaten especially on
Mid-Lent Sunday.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Herrick.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simoniac</ent>⟦br⟧
